so that humanity might know God in an unbroken relationship and a healed relationship.

23:14.779 --> 23:16.120
Well, this is what Jesus Christ does.

23:16.160 --> 23:17.703
He goes to the cross.

23:17.743 --> 23:19.705
He takes the weight of sin upon himself.

23:20.046 --> 23:21.608
He dies.

23:21.648 --> 23:27.416
He's raised from the dead, defeating sin and death and making us, giving us union with Him.

23:28.137 --> 23:34.546
So the Father sends the Son, but then the Son and the Father, they send the Spirit.

23:35.842 --> 23:45.378
They grant the Spirit to continue that work of bearing witness to God in the world, the life, the death, the resurrection of Jesus, the majesty, the holiness of God.

23:46.480 --> 23:51.128
So we are people who, at the core of who we are, we are sent.

23:51.568 --> 23:57.298
As the Father has sent me, so I am sending you, as what Jesus says at the end of John's gospel.

23:57.826 --> 24:01.010
So we are people, we are not about our own business.

24:01.130 --> 24:04.494
We are not about our own purposes in a selfish way.

24:04.534 --> 24:07.478
No, we are people who are about what God wants.

24:07.498 --> 24:09.661
We are people who are about God's purpose.

24:09.681 --> 24:14.387
And that is bearing witness to Christ, bearing witness to God in this world.

24:15.368 --> 24:15.688
Mission.

24:16.409 --> 24:18.272
And then finally, prayer.

24:19.073 --> 24:21.596
It shapes our, it influences our prayer.

24:23.038 --> 24:26.642
And we've been given a connection piece to this triune God.

24:28.546 --> 24:31.629
Jesus says, ask anything in my name.

24:33.211 --> 24:37.615
So if the Father may be glorified, ask anything in my name and I will do it.

24:38.736 --> 24:50.949
As we live these lives of mission, as we bear witness to the Father, to the Son, to the Holy Spirit, as we bear witness to God, Jesus says, ask and I will give it to you.

24:52.090 --> 24:56.274
So when we pray, we know we're not talking to ourselves,

24:56.962 --> 25:01.029
You know, through the power of the Holy Spirit, we are in divine communion.

25:01.831 --> 25:06.740
We're united to the Father, to the Son, through the Holy Spirit in our prayer.

25:06.780 --> 25:13.472
And Jesus, after He's crucified, after He raises from the dead 50 days later, He ascends into heaven.

25:13.492 --> 25:16.097
Well, right now, Jesus Christ, it's weird to think about it.

25:16.117 --> 25:20.164
Jesus Christ in His resurrected flesh, He is at the Father's right hand.

25:20.184 --> 25:21.106
Do you know what He's doing?

25:22.594 --> 25:24.357
He's interceding for us.

25:24.878 --> 25:27.181
He lives to intercede for us.

25:27.822 --> 25:31.027
Jesus Christ, in the book of Hebrews, He's called this high priest.

25:31.628 --> 25:34.392
He is the high priest that is always interceding for us.

25:34.793 --> 25:38.959
So as we pray through the power of the Holy Spirit, Jesus Christ too, He knows our burdens.

25:39.260 --> 25:47.272
He knows our concerns that He knows what we need and He is constantly offering those interceding for us to the Father.

25:50.176 --> 25:51.218
Knowing God,

25:51.522 --> 25:55.466
is eternal life, knowing our triune God.

25:55.526 --> 25:58.049
This is how he has revealed himself to us.

25:58.469 --> 26:01.753
It's all about relationship, knowing God.

26:01.773 --> 26:18.070
So may we, as his people, may we give ourselves to this amazing, awesome, wonderful God, the God who has given himself fully and completely to us, Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.

26:18.791 --> 26:21.394
And all of God's people said, amen.

26:30.530 --> 26:37.620
Take a couple minutes, a couple moments, to let God's words sit with you.

26:38.381 --> 26:40.944
Maybe you wanna think about how you wanna respond to it.

26:41.545 --> 26:42.646
Maybe it's gratitude.

26:43.267 --> 26:50.117
Maybe it's just words of thanksgiving for how awesome and still incomprehensible how mysterious this God is.

26:51.799 --> 26:53.201
Maybe it's an offering of trust.

26:53.301 --> 26:57.106
God, I trust that Jesus himself is God.

26:58.210 --> 27:01.155
and I commit to submitting all of my ways to Him.

27:03.338 --> 27:10.390
Maybe it's trust in the Holy Spirit and the power that the Spirit gives us as we are sent out in mission.

27:10.770 --> 27:16.179
Maybe it's a commitment to the mission that God has, Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.

27:16.500 --> 27:22.930
What is it that you are being called to offer to the Lord in response to who He is?

